ass=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 576<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 9:22:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   PoP and the 6 person group</span><hr size=1> One of the big attractions to me was SoE's claim that PoP would have a lot of content for the 6 person group.<br>
<br>
In one way they were right (at least in the beginning). You do need a group to really hunt effectively, 4 5 6, but the concept was there. It is even truer in the trials were a good group of 6 is really required to win.<br>
<br>
Where it falls off is obatining parchments. The drop rate has been cut back so severly on etheral drops, your lucky to see 1 or 2 in a play session in tier 1 or tier 2 zones.<br>
<br>
It is even worse when it comes to Spectral parchments, they simply are not dropping in tier 1 or tier 2 zones, and I wonder if anyone knows a place where a stardard group of 6 can now hunt to get spectral parchments? IF so are they in a zone that the same group of 6 can access reasonably? PoS/PoV being the 2 zones that require a good group of 6 to access? (I chose these 2 zones, with the reasoning SoE gave before release, that a lot of content would be geared in that direction. Content should also refer to reward, not just exp)These 2 zones were made to be obtainable from a group of 6.<br>
<br>
The trials are fun, and challanging. However once you pass them, with the changes to the drop rates, and locations, those same 6 people will not obtain a Spectral parchment, and the whole scheme breaks down.<br>
<br>
Spells are the life blood of a caster. The trials, are not easy, but they were rewarding, because the drop rates were better in those zones. Risk vs: Reward  in full evidense.<br>
<br>
With the changes, the risk is there, but the reward for casters in the form of spectral parchments, and even etheral parchments are severly lacking or non existant.<br>
<br>
Calebe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=casmx>CasmX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 9:28:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoP and the 6 person group</span><hr size=1> actually, i kinda thought the trials were easy. Okay, pick a rock and tank it, I'll banish the other rock. k, couple nukes here. wow, that waves done, mod up and med <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 12:41:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Trials easy?</span><hr size=1> I dont know about the next set of planes. I have not been able to get flagged yet (guild too low in general, so I have to rely on pick up groups for the trials; play times etc.).<br>
<br>
I cannot say that the trials are easy (execution was the only one I tried so far, about 10 times now). My best group there so far consisted of 61 war, 61 cle, 60 rog, 61 enc, 59 monk and myself (60 mag). In the best (third I think) attempt we made it through second wave (I got aggro then from two mobs and went down fast). We would probably have done it with a few more attempts, but time ran out for some of us so it didnt happen that day.<br>
<br>
If the planes that you can reach after doing the trials do not offer some reasonable reward for the time spent to get to them...something's screwed up. And if the &quot;ideal&quot; group setup you have to have to get through the trial is an indication for the difficulty of the planes after that...I am not looking forward to them. Certainly nice if you are in a strong guild, but not everyone has such people around.<br>
<br>
PoP may have been built for small groups of players, but they definitely didnt have the &quot;average&quot; player in mind then.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 481<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 2:07:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   dumb.....</span><hr size=1> Pop is in my opinion a proof of how little designers and others really play their game.<br>
It has so many flaws that it aint funny.<br>
<br>
First of all, the stupid idea that everything need to do twice as much dmg as before made it near impossible to do anything without a slower. It is as simple as that, if you want a group that can make decent exp you need a slower, no exeptions.<br>
<br>
Second, the lack of good loot, same problem like with Luclin, there are no loot, I can think of one place in Tier 1-2 that drop any kind of loot (that aint a boss kind of mob).<br>
<br>
Third, they added parchments.....   SPELLS SHOULDN'T BE LOOT!!!!! This been a stupidity since Kunark. They now even added focus effects that would been a awesome way of getting casters nice items and upgrades in their loot, items that acctually improved their performance. Spell as loot if  horrible idea.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the best way of getting exp is still to duo. Sad but true, I hoped they would fix group exp bonuses, but they didn't. If you good at quading that still the best exp, if you have a shaman friend you as a mage make an AA rather easy each hour (plenty of mobs that take a min to kill and give about 1.5 blue each).<br>
<br>
Fifth, and this is rather the core......  Designers have no clue how people play this game. <br>
They got the stupid idea that people would work on exp a bit, then work on getting flags, then work AA, then work on getting parchments. <br>
Did this happen?  No, people leveled first, then worried about the rest after. This issue rather destroyed alot of things, getting L63+ spells are near impossible for none big guilded. Alot of L61-L65 spells are a total waste, many got Shield of maelini before Shield of Arcane, total wasted spellslots.<br>
<br>
And last (well from me atleast).<br>
People didn't test stuff enough, there are tons of stuff that look good on paper but not working, bugs that been added and still not fixed.<br>
Some critical bugs, that problaly could be fixed in Beta if it been reported and if Verant cared.<br>
<br>
Bolts graphics not working.<br>
Servant of Ro is green and can't land on anything over L54 or so.<br>
Host of Elements had wrong time in description (or was nerfed).<br>
Host of the elements are green pets with like 10hp each, a rampage or AE destroy them.<br>
You can't heal pet then you have Host or Servnat of Ro up (this make Servant of Ro even more useless at L3).<br>
