I'd make a counterargument for each of your points, but, instead I'll just say that I disagree with every single one of them. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 7:28:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmm...</span><hr size=1> Ehh, the bugg issues I mention are not something you really can disagree with, the stuff simply don't work.<br>
<br>
The same with the issues I listed. Maybe you not agree with spell as loot could be ok, but seeing all the complains about low parchmentdrops on diffrent boards and after people getting 10+ spell duplicates I don't think many like this system.<br>
<br>
You can either argue about not needing a slower, if you not got a slower you are alot less effective.<br>
<br>
You can't argue about not solo or duo is most effective to get exp, thats a simple fact.<br>
<br>
You can't argue about not alot of spells are a waste and a proof about the designer had no clue about how people play the game. How many here was L63 before they got either Shield or Arcane or Shield of Maelini? Or even got Shield of Maelini first? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tainsumnr>Tain Sumnr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 8:41:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoP and the 6 person group</span><hr size=1> Oh, come on...<br>
<br>
There are only so many ways to make encounters hard, without being impossible.  <br>
<br>
-A ton of hp with lowered damage output.<br>
-High damage output with lowered hp.<br>
-Mediocre swarms of mobs.<br>
<br>
We had seen the incredible boredom that was high hp mobs with luclin..we begged them to get rid of it.  They did...but, how do you do that without reverting back to 3 year old content that is trivial? High damage output...<br>
<br>
Also, healing was a non-issue for most of luclin grouping.  An afterthough basically.  You got the highest dps group possible and threw in whatever healer happened to be around...sometimes you didn't even bother with that.  High damage mobs bring healing back as a much more vital part of groups...something priest classes, specifically clerics, needed.  <br>
<br>
Finally, this setup favors casters much more then long drawn out battles.  Its much more realistic for us to keep up high dps's over short fights...then the endless ones of old.  High damage, low hp mobs have always been the shining point of damage casters.  <br>
<br>
Anyways, it appears you play as much as you accuse verant of.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 484<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 10:48:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Other options..</span><hr size=1> Making it near impossible to single pull mobs and make them unrottable and unmezzable would been alot better solution. <br>
This would force groups to get bigger groups and most of all figure out ways to handle with adds.<br>
<br>
The holy trinity wouldn't be needed in that case, but the solution Verant chosed forced any L65 group that want good exp to have a slower. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=apollonike>apollonike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 6:32:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Other options..</span><hr size=1> I don't see why spells shouldn't be loot.  Equipment is the lifeblood of a melee, and they need loot to upgrade.  Spells are the lifeblood for casters, why should it be free while melee has to work for their upgrades?<br>
<br>
That being said, parchaments do need to be a bit more common...the current system does need to be looked at.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
kegulik <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 578<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 8:16:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Other options..</span><hr size=1> Apollonike,<br>
<br>
I don't see why spells shouldn't be loot. Equipment is the lifeblood of a melee, and they need loot to upgrade. Spells are the lifeblood for casters, why should it be free while melee has to work for their upgrades?<br>
<br>
<br>
This is not true, Casters also need equipement to be better. A caster with FT15 is way better off than a caster with FT 4 or 5. Equipement does matter.<br>
<br>
Who is better off, a mage with BoBc? Or a magician without them?<br>
<br>
To say a caster doesn't need equipement is wrong, we need equipement, and spells. <br>
<br>
Calebe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 561<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 8:39:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8011.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Other options..</span><hr size=1> No, I can disagree with every single point in the post, and I do. They were all opinions. I obviously have to agree that every group &quot;needs&quot; a slower. Where I disagree with you is that you clearly imply that you find it to be a problem. I don't.<br>
<br>
Which brings me to something I only half disagree with you with, is the parchments being loot. I think spells being loot is a good idea. The problem I have with the spell loot system is that it's too hard. That brings us back to what I think is the original topic of this thread... spectrals can't really be done by a 6 person group.<br>
<br>
